cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.CR 

The paper focuses on generating local explanations for individual predictions in tree-based ensembles, specifically Gradient Boosting Decision Trees (GBDTs). This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of GBDTs in computer vision (cs.CV) and the need to account for sequential dependency between trees (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of existing methods for counterfactual explanations, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
